summary: Broadchurch ep 4&5 Thoughts (that aren’t deep so)
body:
Broadchurch ep 4&5 Thoughts (that aren’t deep so)

Man. Broadchurch is…idek man. But I love it. It’s so good.

  • Alec trying to be social is actually me okay. “I didn’t know which to get, so I got them all.” Wkkdosndkdkdodn. I feel bro.
  • On the note of Alec, the pre-beard or whatever is going on there is growing on me tbh. I don’t hate it,,
  • Beth. Beth Beth Beth. I know i said it in a previous post but DADGUM JODIE WHITTAKER. *applause* Seeing her as thirteen and then Beth is a crazy difference but she does it so well. Ugh. Love her.
  • Karen is growing on me, despite. And honestly i like her and Olly together. But—idk I feel like she might leave him in the dust. I guess I’ll see.
  • Becca. I think I want to like her but…UGH. you just DONT SLEEP WITH A MARRIED MAN WITH CHILDREN.
  • also still not sure how I feel about mark….just—not sure.
  • Although the end scene with he and Beth looking through Danny’s stuff gave me Feels™
  • Alec warming up to Miller and kind of softening to her makes me happy. And the dinner when he and Mr. Miller are laughing…Bros. Just be Bros, ‘Kay?
  • As to who I’m thinking did it…I’m not gonna say. Mostly because I hate being wrong. I’m sure me not telling as anything to do with the fact I’m so caught up in theory’s i have no idea. Shhh.

More more more!!!! I want to watch more!!!

OH AND, I love Arthur Darvill in this!!!
